So I was in Zuccotti Park during the Occupy
Movement quite a bit and after the Mayor of

00:37:24.290 --> 00:37:29.850
Bloomberg attempted to seize the park and
failed, it was clear to the activist that

00:37:29.850 --> 00:37:31.310
they would come again.

00:37:31.310 --> 00:37:36.070
But this time they would come without any
warning, probably as they did in the middle

00:37:36.070 --> 00:37:37.490
of the night.

00:37:37.490 --> 00:37:47.670
CH: And so the direct action committee wanted
to prepare some kind of surprise for the NYPD.

00:37:47.670 --> 00:37:52.980
So they all came down to my house in Princeton
slept all over my floor.

00:37:52.980 --> 00:37:56.480
And everybody sat at the dining room table.

00:37:56.480 --> 00:38:00.230
All electronic devices were, this was before
Snowden.

00:38:00.230 --> 00:38:02.430
All, they were very prescient.

00:38:02.430 --> 00:38:05.089
All electronic devices were put in the car.

00:38:05.089 --> 00:38:07.900
Phones, computers, everything in the car in
the driveway.

00:38:07.900 --> 00:38:08.900
Nobody spoke.

00:38:08.900 --> 00:38:12.290
Everybody wrote on pieces of paper and handed
them back and forth and then we burned them

00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:14.359
in the fireplace.

00:38:14.359 --> 00:38:15.359
[laughter]

00:38:15.359 --> 00:38:23.859
CH: And when the NYPD came, they stormed the
park and it was pretty brutal.

00:38:23.859 --> 00:38:28.430
And they got to the kitchen area in the center
of the park, and they found 20 activists chained

00:38:28.430 --> 00:38:31.880
to the kitchen and they didn't have chain
cutters.

00:38:31.880 --> 00:38:36.640
And that was a big, it was like, you don't
