They got the right people.

00:39:23.580 --> 00:39:28.730
They were taking them and fabricating felony
convictions against them.

00:39:28.730 --> 00:39:30.760
Then forcing them to plea out.

00:39:30.760 --> 00:39:41.829
So, for instance, one activist was charged
with holding a pair of scissors, and carrying

00:39:41.829 --> 00:39:46.170
out what was called an attempted assault,
a deadly assault against a police officer.

00:39:46.170 --> 00:39:49.000
Now they filmed Zuccotti 24 hours a day.

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:56.400
CH: But of course they didn't film that assault
because it didn't exist.

00:39:56.400 --> 00:39:59.579
And it was his word against the cops.

00:39:59.579 --> 00:40:02.990
And he had to plea out on a five year felony
conviction.

00:40:02.990 --> 00:40:07.340
Which means, that if they pick him up for
anything else he goes to prison for seven

00:40:07.340 --> 00:40:08.340
years.

00:40:08.340 --> 00:40:13.769
And that was a very effective technique to
neuter the best activist.

00:40:13.769 --> 00:40:14.769
There's a very...

00:40:14.769 --> 00:40:17.000
It's very dark what's happening.

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:22.990
It's subterranean because all of the resistance
